Steps to create proxy

1 - Obtain the Make and Model number for your device
        ex: Make - Tripplite, Model - PDUMH20
        Ensure this is desciptive and unique to the specific device(s) you intend your proxy for.

2 - Rename the following files. Remain consistent with captialization of placeholder.
        This ensures that all variable names will match up.
        src/csi_make_model
        src/make_model/make_model_settings.py
        src/make_model/make_model_mocker.py
        src/test/test_snmp_poller_make_model.py
        src/test/test_snmp_setter_make_model.py

3 - Fill in Make and Model throughout files. Remain consistent with captialization of placeholder.
        This ensures that all variable names will match up.
        If you make changes, make sure to make them consistent and test by building the proxy.
        ex: csi_make_model -> csi_tripplite_pdumh20
        ex: MakeMODELSettings -> TripplitePDUMH20Settings

        Placeholders can be found by searching for 'csi/make', csi_make, 'makemodel', 'make_model'
        'Make CSI', 'MAKE_MOCK' and 'Make Model' or by making all the replacements in the following files:

        .env   
                PROXY_NAME=csi_make_model
                SVC_NAME=csi_make_model_0
        csi_properties.yml     
                service_name: csi_make_model_0
        pyproject.toml
                name = "csi_make_model"
                description = "FastAPI-based proxy for Make Model"
        jupyter/test_harness.ipynb
                SERVICE_URL = maestro_url + '/service/csi_make_model_0'
        src/csi_make_model/__init__.py
                from .make_model_settings import MakeMODELSettings
                from .make_model_mocker import MAKE_TEST
        src/csi_make_model/main.py
                from make_model_settings import MakeMODELSettings
