4 - Other updates that will need to be made:
        .env    # Replace with a unique port
                SVC_PORT_INT=81XX
                SVC_PORT_EXT=81XX
                # Add DBPASS if needed
                DBPASS=example
        csi_properties.yml      #update fields for your requirements and comms information
                heartbeat_interval_msecs: [default: 5]
                keepalive_secs: [default: 60]
                poll_interval: [default: 60]

                debug_mode: ['OFF'] #see csi_properties.yml for more information

                default_ip_address: [device ip]
                default_snmp_version: [1, 2 or 3]
                default_read_community: [typically public]
                default_write_community: [typically private]
        README.md      
                Update status date and text to be descriptive of your device.

5 - Test build to ensure your names are correct and everything works as expected.
        $ make all

6 - Obtain the MIB(s) for your device, place into 'mibs' directory

7 - Test MIBs using snmpwalk and snmpset to find MIBs that work and match fields in the DoF.

8 - snmp to dof mapping and settings file
        Add mappings to the schemas/snmp_to_dof_mapping.yml file in the format of the provided example.
        Mappings must all be inside the 'properties' field.
        ex:
                exampleMIB:
                        #set to true if MIB has an OID index, false or omit if not
                        use_oid_index: true
                        #required: map to DoF name
                        dof_name:
                        example.ports.status
                        #set to true for R/W fields, false or omit if not
                        settable: true
        OIDs to be polled to retrieve the wanted MIBs should be provided at the bottom using 
        the 'polled_oids' field
        ex:
                polled_oids:
                        - example
                        - example2

9 - custom code
        Each field in the DoF is only complete if there is a 1:1 mapping with a MIB.
        Sometimes fields require some custom code to match the DoF.
        For example, if the units are different they will need to be changed to match
        or when two MIB values are needed to fulfil one DoF value, like when one field
        is used for reading and one for writing. Both examples are shown below and a more
        in depth explanation of the code can be viewed in the tutorial.

10 - Test proxy using jupyter notebook test harness.
        Launch the jupyter notebook:
        $ cd jupyter
        $ ./launcher.sh
        Click on the first box and click play on each until you reach the bottom.
        Ensure there are no errors and at the bottom there should be a box where you can send
        test JSON to your proxy, and one where you can test snmp commands.
